# /list-tasks — fetch open tasks from {{TASK_MANAGER}}

This skill is generated by `/process-setup` and lives at `.claude/skills/list-tasks/SKILL.md` in the consumer repo. It is invoked by the `/process` clarification skill via the Skill tool to populate the task picker.

The configured task manager for this repo is **{{TASK_MANAGER}}** (slug: `{{TASK_MANAGER_SLUG}}`).

## Output contract

Return a list of tasks, one per line, in this exact format so the caller can parse it:

```
<id>\t<title>\t<one-line description>
```

Tab-separated. Up to 20 tasks. Sorted by priority (highest first) if the API supports it; otherwise by recency.

If there are no open tasks, print a single line:

```
(no open tasks)
```

If credentials are missing or the API call fails, print to stderr a one-line error starting with `LIST_TASKS_ERROR:` and exit non-zero. The caller will fall back to asking the user to describe a task manually.

