## Notes for the caller

- Each emitted line is `<id>\t<title>\t<description>`. The caller should split on the first two tabs only — the description may itself contain spaces (it must NOT contain newlines or tabs; the commands above strip them).
- The `id` is opaque to the /process skill except for prefixing with the manager slug. Never let the id contain whitespace or shell metacharacters — the commands above all read from API responses, not user input, so this is safe.
- If you change the task manager later, re-run `/process-setup` and pick a different one. This file will be regenerated.
